        <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-one-third">
            <h2 class="nhsuk-heading-s nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-3"><a href="/patterns/inset-text">Inset text</a></h2>
            <p>Help users identify and understand important content on the page, even if they don't read the whole page.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-one-third">
            <h2 class="nhsuk-heading-s nhsuk-u-margin-bottom-3"><a href="/patterns/warning-callout">Warning callout</a></h2>
            <p>Designed to stand out from the rest of the content.</p>   
        </div>
    </div>



  <div class="nhsuk-grid-row">
    <div class="nhsuk-grid-column-two-thirds nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">



										
            <h2>Tested NHS.UK look and feel styles</h2>

            <p>We know that these patterns help users find what they need. They will also make your service consistent with other NHS services.</p>

            <p>We are continuing to test and improve them and we are working on new patterns, including components for forms. If you can’t find what you want here, contact us on the <a href="https://nhsuk.slack.com/messages/standards">NHS.UK #standards Slack channel</a> or email the standards team at <a href="mailto:service-manual@nhs.net"> service-manual@nhs.net</a>.</p>



            <h2 class="nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">Creating or changing patterns</h2>

            <p>You're welcome to adapt one of these patterns or to create a new one. Check with us first on the <a href="https://nhsuk.slack.com/messages/standards">NHS.UK #standards Slack channel</a> or email us at <a href="mailto:service-manual@nhs.net"> service-manual@nhs.net</a>. We may already be working on what you need.</p>
      
            <p>Help improve the manual by contributing your work.</p>


            <h2 class="nhsuk-u-margin-top-8">Why use patterns?</h2>

            <p>Following design patterns means you can:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>avoid repeating work done by other teams</li>
                    <li>build on the research and experience of other teams</li>
                    <li>make your service consistent with other NHS services</li>
                </ul>





  





   

  



